HEADWORD: Aberrate
<hw>Ab"er*rate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aberratus</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>aberrare</ets>; <ets>ab</ets> +
<ets>errare</ets> to wander. See <er>Err</er>.]</ety> <def>To go astray;
to diverge.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their own defective and <qex>aberrating</qex> vision.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aberration</ent>⟦br⟧
